<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-29T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-29T02:00:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4314: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-29T15:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">April 29,
                                        1922—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 29—9:20
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>177. I recommend that regiment at Tientsin be brought up to strength
                            authorized in new organization which would require an addition of 375
                            men. This is recommended by commander expeditionary force, military
                            attaché and naval attaché.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>